ce:section.ce:para:
HL-60 cells were cultured in Dulbecco’s modified Eagle’s medium (DMEM) containing 10% fetal bovine serum (FBS) in a humidified atmosphere containing 5% CO2 at 37 °C. CCK-8 assay was utilized to determine the cell viability without and with NIR irradiation. Briefly, HL-60 cells were seeded in a 96-well plate at a concentration of 1 × 104 cells per well and cultured in a humidified 5% CO2 atmosphere at 37 °C before use, and the volume of the cell suspension loaded in each well is 100 μL. After that, Au/GQDs/Cyt/MPA/PEI and Au/GQDs/MPA/PEI of different concentrations were added and incubated with the cell medium without and with NIR irradiation. In the case of NIR irradiation, the NIR irradiation was performed for 10 min. After 12 h of incubation, 10 μL of CCK-8 solution was added into each well to incubate for another 3 h. The absorbance in each well was measured at the wavelength of 450 nm to calculate the number of viable cells, and the relative cell viability was determined according to the following equation: Inhibition rate (%) = [(Acontrol
                         − Aexperiment
                        )/Acontrol
                        ] × 100, where the control cells were treated with an equal volume of DMEM without the addition of Au/GQDs/Cyt/MPA/PEI and Au/GQDs/MPA/PEI. Three multiple holes were set for every sample.
